result.execSummary:
The defendant Michelle L. Quechol was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Michelle L. Quechol is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Michelle L. Quechol was found guilty of Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Defendant Michelle L. Quechol in court with attorney Margaret Waterman on behalf of attorney Timothy Henney.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Defendant to enter plea to Ct 1.  State will move to dismiss Cts 2-3.  Atty Waterman agrees.  Defendant enters Guilty plea to Ct 1.  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct 1.  Counts 2-3 are ordered dismissed.
Counsel make sentencing arguments.
BY THE COURT:  Court sentences defendant to serve 30 days in the Marquette County Jail, consecutive to any sentence she may now be serving.  Sentence to commenct on or before 3/18/16, clean and sober.  Huber granted.  Granted 2 days credit; however, if there are additions, counsel will stipulate.  May be served in Sauk County.
